        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Since we're managing the import process, let's use this approach.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>We need two pieces of information to connect PolyBase to the Azure Storage account:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The URL of the storage account</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The private storage key</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Use the Azure portal to get both of these values.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This exercise is optional.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If you don't have an Azure account, or prefer not to do the exercise in your account, read the instructions to understand how to retrieve the access keys to an Azure Storage account.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Sign in to the <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Azure portal<ept id="p1">](https://portal.azure.com?azure-portal=true)</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Storage account, under <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Settings<ept id="p1">**</ept>, select <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Access keys<ept id="p2">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Access keys<ept id="p1">**</ept> blade, copy the value of <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>key1<ept id="p2">**</ept> and save it to a temporary file.</source>
